intermedia.ru/news/333202 \u0415\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u0438\u043b\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0438 \u041c\u0430\u0440\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430 \u0421\u043f\u0438\u0432\u0430\u043a \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u043e\u044e\u0442 \u00ab\u0428\u0438\u0444\u0440\u00bb \u043d\u0430 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u043c \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0435]</ref><ref>[https://echo.msk.ru/programs/beseda/34937/ \u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044c\u044e: \u041b\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u041a\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0446\u043e\u0432\u0430]</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nThe film tells about the relationship of the French baron Paul de Russo and the modest translator Anna from a quiet provincial town.<ref>[https://www.kinopoisk.ru/film/84998/ \u0424\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0443\u0437]<r/ref\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Mikhail Efremov]] as Karpienko\n* [[Ekaterina Filippova]]\n* [[:ru:\u0413\u043e\u043b\u0443\u0431\u043a\u0438\u043d\u0430, \u041c\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0430|Mariya Golubkina]] as Anya\n* [[Thierry Monfray]]\n* [[Dmitriy Orlov]]\n* Sergei Popov as Anya's Father\n* [[Irina Rakhmanova]] as Passenger\n* [[Nina Ruslanova]] as Anya's Mother\n* [[Garik Sukachyov]]\n* [[Zoya Tolbuzina]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|1}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0409979}}\n\n[[Category:2004 films]]\n[[Category:Russian-language films]]\n[[Category:Russian comedy  films]]\n[[Category:Russian films]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toMikhail Yefremov(link changed toMikhail Yefremov (actor); link changed toMikhail Yefremov (actor)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_French_Guy"}
{"title_page": "It's Russian", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name = It's Russian\n| film name = {{lang-ru|\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435}}\n| image =\n| caption = \n| director = [[:ru:\u0412\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447|Aleksandr Veledinsky]]\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Aleksei Alyakin\n* Sergey Chliyants\n* Maksim Lagashkin\n}}\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Eduard Limonov]]\n* [[Aleksandr Veledinskiy]]\n}}\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Andrey Chadov]]\n* [[Olga Arntgolts]]\n* [[Evdokiya Germanova]]\n* [[Mikhail Yefremov (actor)|Mikhail Efremov]]\n* [[Vladimir Steklov]]\n}}\n| music = [[Aleksey Zubarev]]\n| cinematography = [[Pavel Ignatov]]\n| editing = Tatyana Prilenskaya\n| released = \n| studio= \n| runtime = \n| country = [[Russia]]\n| language = Russian\n| budget = \n}}\n'''''It's Russian''''' ({{lang-ru|\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435}}) is a 2004 Russian comedy film directed by [[:ru:\u0412\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447|Aleksandr Veledinsky]].<ref>[https://rg.ru/2020/03/17/umer-eduard-limonov.html \u0423\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u042d\u0434\u0443\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u041b\u0438\u043c\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432]</ref><ref>[https://www.kino-teatr.ru/kino/news/y2020/3-17/20705/ \u0423\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0438 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0438\u043a \u042d\u0434\u0443\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u041b\u0438\u043c\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432]</ref><ref>[https://www.amic.ru/voprosdnya/457046/ \u0412\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0431\u0443\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440\u044c \u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440. \u0427\u0442\u043e \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u0441\u0435\u0431\u044f \u042d\u0434\u0443\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u041b\u0438\u043c\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432]</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nEdik Savenko wants to go to a restaurant with the girl, but his parents do not give him money. To get them, he robs the dining room, then gets drunk. Seeing a girl with another guy, he cuts his veins.<ref>[https://www.kinopoisk.ru/film/254806/ \u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435]</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Andrey Chadov]] as Ed\n* [[Olga Arntgolts]] as Svetka\n* [[Evdokiya Germanova]] as Mother\n* [[Mikhail Yefremov (actor)|Mikhail Efremov]] as Father\n* [[Vladimir Steklov]] as Zilberman\n* [[Aleksey Gorbunov]] as Gorkun\n* [[Dmitry Dyuzhev]] as Slavka\n* [[Anatoliy Zalyubovsky]] as Kadik\n* [[Oleg Lopukhov]] as Sanya\n* [[Viktor Rakov]] as Mikhaylov\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|1}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0834948}}\n\n[[Category:2004 films]]\n[[Category:Russian-language films]]\n[[Category:Russian comedy films]]\n[[Category:Russian films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name = It's Russian\n| film name = {{lang-ru|\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435}}\n| image =\n| caption = \n| director = [[:ru:\u0412\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447|Aleksandr Veledinsky]]\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Aleksei Alyakin\n* Sergey Chliyants\n* Maksim Lagashkin\n}}\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Eduard Limonov]]\n* [[Aleksandr Veledinskiy]]\n}}\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Andrey Chadov]]\n* [[Olga Arntgolts]]\n* [[Evdokiya Germanova]]\n* [[Mikhail Efremov]]\n* [[Vladimir Steklov]]\n}}\n| music = [[Aleksey Zubarev]]\n| cinematography = [[Pavel Ignatov]]\n| editing = Tatyana Prilenskaya\n| released = \n| studio= \n| runtime = \n| country = [[Russia]]\n| language = Russian\n| budget = \n}}\n'''''It's Russian''''' ({{lang-ru|\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435}}) i